                    <head>Fourteen folios of paintings and calligraphy from an album of assembled at
                        Lucknow for Swiss mercenary Antoine Polier (d. 1795).</head>
                    <msContents>

                        <summary>Fourteen folios of forty Persian and South Asian paintings and
                            calligraphy detached from an album assembled for Swiss mercenary
                                <persName role="pat ins" key="person_7537069"
                                ref="https://viaf.org/viaf/7537069/">Colonel Antoine-Louis-Henri
                                Polier (d. 1795)</persName>, probably at <placeName
                                ref="http://vocab.getty.edu/page/tgn/7001561" key="place_7001561"
                                >Lucknow</placeName> and overseen by artist <persName
                                ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/309815013" key="person_309815013"
                                role="ctb cmp art">Mihr Chand</persName>, between <date
                                calendar="#Gregorian" from="1780" to="1787">1780 to 1787</date>.
                            Disordered from its original sequence, the opening folio (now found on
                                <locus from="9b" to="9b">9b</locus>) states the original album
                            contained forty leaves. Despite its incomplete and rebound condition, it
                            still constitutes one of twenty-one of Polier's albums that survive
                            today.</summary>

                        <msItem xml:id="Indian_Drawings_12-item1">
                            <locus from="1a" to="1a">Folio 1a</locus>
                            <title>Blank Folio</title>
                            <textLang mainLang="fa">Persian</textLang>
